# .shellcheckrc ‚Äî shared shellcheck config for the toolkit's shell code.
#
# NOTE: shellcheck has NO `severity` key in .shellcheckrc ‚Äî severity is CLI-ONLY (`-S`/`--severity`).
# A `severity=warning` line here is silently ignored, so the warning FLOOR must live in the callers:
# `.github/scripts/lint-shell.sh` and `.github/workflows/ci.yml` both pass `-S warning`. Only `disable`
# is honored from this file. (An earlier version of this file claimed `severity=warning` here "changes
# no behavior ‚Äî a local run matches CI"; it did NOT ‚Äî bare `shellcheck` fell to its `style` default and
# failed on info/style findings CI never saw.)
#
# SC1090/SC1091: "can't follow non-constant / not-included source". Every lib is sourced by a
# runtime-resolved path (`. .claude/lib/_x.sh`) that shellcheck can't statically follow; that's by
# design, not a bug. Disabled repo-wide (matches CI's `-e SC1090,SC1091`).
disable=SC1090,SC1091
